## Objective

Implement TestE2E_SuccessfulLoginAndSessionPersistence - verify user can log in via Keycloak SSO and session persists across page reloads.

## Test Specification

From specs/007-webapp-auth/TESTING.md lines 63-72.

## Implementation

Create `tests/e2e/sso-login-session-persistence.spec.ts`:

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
import { loginSSO, verifySessionPersists } from './helpers';
import { TEST_USERS } from './fixtures';

test.describe('SSO Login and Session Persistence', () => {
  test('should log in via SSO and maintain session across page reloads', async ({ page }) => {
    // Step 1: Navigate to webapp
    await page.goto('/');

    // Step 2: Click "Sign In" button
    await page.click('button:has-text("Sign In")');

    // Step 3: Assert redirected to Keycloak login page
    await expect(page).toHaveURL(/keycloak.*auth/);

    // Step 4: Enter credentials for alice@example.com
    await page.fill('input[name="username"]', TEST_USERS.productEngineer.username);
    await page.fill('input[name="password"]', TEST_USERS.productEngineer.password);
    await page.click('input[type="submit"]');

    // Step 5: Assert redirected back to webapp dashboard
    await page.waitForURL('/dashboard');
    await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');

    // Step 6: Verify welcome message like "Welcome, Alice" is visible
    await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="user-welcome"]')).toContainText('Alice');

    // Step 7: Reload page and assert user is still logged in
    await page.reload();
    await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');
    await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="user-welcome"]')).toContainText('Alice');

    // Verify session cookie exists
    const cookies = await page.context().cookies();
    const sessionCookie = cookies.find(c => c.name === 'grid.session');
    expect(sessionCookie).toBeDefined();
    expect(sessionCookie?.httpOnly).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- Test navigates to webapp and clicks login
- Browser redirects to Keycloak login page
- User enters credentials and submits
- Browser redirects back to webapp dashboard via OAuth callback
- Dashboard displays user's name
- Page reload maintains session (no re-authentication required)
- Session cookie is HttpOnly and present
- Test passes consistently

